  "summary": "Decision quality matters more than information volume.",
  "body": "Joz evaluates systems through the lens of decisions.\n\nKey questions include:\n\n- What decision is being made?\n- Who owns it?\n- What information supports it?\n- How trustworthy is the information?\n- What happens if the decision is wrong?\n- How quickly can the organization act?\n\nMany organizational problems appear to be technology problems but are actually decision problems.\n\nImproving decision quality often creates disproportionate business value.",
